Type: Package
Package: dRiftDM
Title: Fitting and Exploring Drift Diffusion Models
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Valentin", "Koob", , "koob@uni-bremen.de", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person("Thomas", "Richter", role = "aut"),
    person("Markus", "Janczyk", role = "aut")
  )
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Description: Drift Diffusion models (DDMs) are common in cognitive psychology to 
  desribe decision processes in simple tasks. We provide a wrapper around 
  the numerical solutions summarized by Richter et al. (2023) to easily apply
  DDMs via Maximum-Likelihood-Estimation.
